<main style="font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; padding: 48px 20px; max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto;">
  <header style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap: 16px;">
    <div style="font-weight:700; font-size: 18px;">Smart Tinmen</div>

    <nav style="display:flex; gap: 14px; font-size: 14px;">
      <a href="#services" style="text-decoration:none;">Services</a>
      <a href="#work" style="text-decoration:none;">Work</a>
      <a href="#process" style="text-decoration:none;">Process</a>
      <a href="#founders" style="text-decoration:none;">Founders</a>
      <a href="#contact" style="text-decoration:none;">Contact</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <section style="padding: 56px 0 28px;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 44px; line-height: 1.1; margin: 0 0 14px;">
      We build working prototypes for real-world robotics & connected devices.
    </h1>

    <p style="font-size: 18px; max-width: 66ch; margin: 0 0 22px; opacity: 0.85;">
      Smart Tinmen is a prototyping studio spanning electronics, embedded systems, and software.
      We turn uncertain ideas into testable builds—so you can validate fast, demo confidently, and de-risk the next step.
    </p>

    <div style="display:flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <a href="#contact"
         style="display:inline-block; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: #111; color: #fff; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600;">
        Tell us about your project
      </a>
      <a href="#work"
         style="display:inline-block; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; color: #111; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600;">
        See examples
      </a>
    </div>

    <div style="display:flex; gap: 10px; margin-top: 18px; font-size: 13px; opacity: 0.7; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <span>• 1–2 week proof-of-concept</span>
      <span>• Electronics + firmware</span>
      <span>• Robotics / sensing / integration</span>
      <span>• Deployment-focused engineering</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 28px 0;">

  <section id="services" style="padding: 10px 0 30px;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 20px; margin: 0 0 12px;">Services</h2>

    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 14px;">
      <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px;">
        <div style="font-weight:700;">Prototype builds</div>
        <p style="margin: 8px 0 0; opacity: 0.85;">
          From concept to working demo: electronics, firmware, and software that runs outside the lab.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px;">
        <div style="font-weight:700;">Systems & integration</div>
        <p style="margin: 8px 0 0; opacity: 0.85;">
          Sensors, power, comms, data pipelines, and reliability under real constraints.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px;">
        <div style="font-weight:700;">De-risking & technical reviews</div>
        <p style="margin: 8px 0 0; opacity: 0.85;">
          Feasibility checks, architecture review, test plans, and a clear build roadmap.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="work" style="padding: 10px 0 30px;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 20px; margin: 0 0 12px;">Work</h2>
    <p style="margin: 0 0 12px; opacity: 0.85;">
      Add 2–3 case studies here (a photo + 3 bullets each is enough). Placeholders for now:
    </p>

    <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 18px; opacity: 0.85;">
      <li>Sensor + firmware proof-of-concept for a field device (10 days)</li>
      <li>Robotics data capture + processing pipeline for constrained environments (2–3 weeks)</li>
      <li>Demo-ready prototype for stakeholder validation (2 weeks)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="process" style="padding: 10px 0 30px;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 20px; margin: 0 0 12px;">Process</h2>

    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 14px;">
      <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px;">
        <div style="font-weight:700;">1) Scope</div>
        <p style="margin: 8px 0 0; opacity: 0.85;">
          A short kickoff to define constraints, success criteria, timeline, and deliverables.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px;">
        <div style="font-weight:700;">2) Build</div>
        <p style="margin: 8px 0 0; opacity: 0.85;">
          Rapid iterations across hardware + software, with weekly demos and clear checkpoints.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px;">
        <div style="font-weight:700;">3) Test</div>
        <p style="margin: 8px 0 0; opacity: 0.85;">
          Designed for real conditions: reliability, power, sensing quality, and failure modes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px;">
        <div style="font-weight:700;">4) Handover</div>
        <p style="margin: 8px 0 0; opacity: 0.85;">
          Working demo + documentation + next-step recommendations (manufacture, pilot, or productization).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="founders" style="padding: 10px 0 30px;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 20px; margin: 0 0 12px;">Founders</h2>

    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 14px;">
      <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px; display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items:center;">
        <%= image_tag "HL_picture.jpg",
              alt: "Harold Loop — CEO",
              style: "width: 72px; height: 72px; border-radius: 999px; object-fit: cover; border: 1px solid #eee;" %>

        <div>
          <div style="font-weight: 700;">Harold Loop</div>
          <div style="opacity: 0.75; font-size: 14px;">CEO — Delivery, clients, and project execution</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px; display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items:center;">
        <%= image_tag "MDH_picture.jpg",
              alt: "Matthieu de Hemptinne — CTO",
              style: "width: 72px; height: 72px; border-radius: 999px; object-fit: cover; border: 1px solid #eee;" %>

        <div>
          <div style="font-weight: 700;">Matthieu de Hemptinne</div>
          <div style="opacity: 0.75; font-size: 14px;">CTO — Robotics, embedded systems, and software architecture</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="contact" style="padding: 10px 0 40px;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 20px; margin: 0 0 12px;">Contact</h2>
    <p style="margin: 0 0 14px; opacity: 0.85;">
      Send 3 bullets: what you’re building, what “working” means, and your timeline. We’ll reply with a scope + estimate.
    </p>

    <div style="border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px;">
      <p style="margin: 0 0 8px;"><strong>Email:</strong> hello@smarttinmen.com</p>
      <p style="margin: 0; opacity: 0.8;">(Replace with your real email when ready)</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer style="padding-top: 10px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; opacity: 0.7; font-size: 13px;">
    © <%= Time.current.year %> Smart Tinmen
  </footer>
</main>
